column5: Didn't find much when I searched this forum. Anybody stayed at Leuenberger's Jemar Lake outpost? How were the accommodations, size/numbers of walleyes, etc. Thanks in advance.

Not sure if this helps or not since we were there in 1988. Cabin was very rough. Lots and lots of mice sleeping with us every night. Fishing was decent for walleyes, but nothing really big. Caught lots of eaters. Some large northerns. Caught a good amount of the walleyes very close to the cabin. We used only artificials and fished in early-mid September. Probably not much help.
